'''''Why Is It So?''''' is an educational science series produced in [[Australia]] by [[ABC Television]] from 1963 to 1986. The series was hosted by American scientist [[Julius Sumner Miller]], who demonstrated experiments in the world of [[physics]] and [[chemistry]]. <ref>http://www.abc.net.au/science/features/whyisitso/</ref> The series was also screened in the [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[New Zealand]] and in Europe. <ref>http://www.abc.net.au/science/features/whyisitso/about.htm</ref>
This program was based on his 1959 series ''[[Julius Sumner Miller#Television|Why Is It So?]]'' in the United States on [[KCBS-TV|KNXT]] Channel 2 in [[Los Angeles]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.film.queensu.ca/CBC/W.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527160858/http://www.film.queensu.ca/CBC/W.html |archivedate=2010-05-27 |df= }} Why is it so? 4 Sep–23 Oct 1960</ref>
